Animal Outcomes in Austin Animal Shelters Pt. 2¶

Below data from the Austin Animal Shelter system will be analyzed for correlations between the outcomes of animals and their animal type, age, and sex. This section includes data transformations and graphs.

(there was some weirdness going on when I had to convert my strings which is why it is split into two parts)

animal = pd.read_csv("//Users//audreydahlkemper//Downloads//A1//Austin_Animal_Center_Outcomes.csv")

I collected data on Animal Shelters in the Austin Area, 12 intitial variables are represented: Animal ID, Name, DateTime, MonthYear, DOB, Outcome Type, Animal Type, Sex upon Outcome, Age upon Outcome, Breed, and Color.

The first step I took was limiting the extent of the data in order to produce more refined results. Below the number of rows are limited from ~144,000 to 2,000. Each row represents a different animal's outcome. Further down I also limited the amount of columns. Dropping Animal ID, Name, DateTime, DOB, and Color. This reduced the column variables from 12 to 7.

Due to the spacing between the column names I chose to rename the data sets in order to be able to transform the information into int/float values.

In [12]:

Animal Outcome Key: 0=Rto-Adopt, 1=Adoption, 2=Euthenasia, 3=Transfer, 4=Return to Owner, 5=Died, 6=Discarded

Animal Type Key: 0=Other, 1=Dog, 2=Cat, 3=Bird

Confirms findings from pt.1, dogs have the highest adoption rates and cats have the highest transfer rates.

In [50]:
w=0.4
x= ['Adopted', 'Transfered', 'Returned to Owner', 'Euthanized', 'Died']
Dogs = [562, 228, 287, 30, 6]
Cats = [381, 302, 31, 35, 12]
plt.figure(figsize=(10,12))

plt.bar(x,Dogs,w,label='Dogs')
plt.bar(x,Cats,w,label='Cats')

plt.xlabel("Different Outcomes")
plt.ylabel("Number of Animals")
plt.title("The Relationship between Different Types of Animals and Austin Animal Shelter Outcomes")


plt.legend()
plt.show()

Adoption, transfer, return, euthanization, and death between cats vs dogs. Dogs maintain the highest adoption rate and the highest return to owner rate.
